Sunlight: Full sun to partial shade

Soil: Well-drained, moderately fertile

Watering: Moderate; avoid waterlogging

Propagation: By seed or division of clumps

ğŸŒ¼ Symbolism & Uses

Symbolism: Innocence, purity, loyal love

Medicinal uses: Traditionally used in teas or poultices for minor wounds and digestion

Decorative: Popular in gardens, bouquets, and wildflower meadows
